article.headline: Old Dominion 74, James Madison 72
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Kent Bazemore scored 19 points and had six assists as Old Dominion edged James Madison 74-72 in a Colonial Athletic Association game on Wednesday night. Bazemore assisted on Frank Hassell's dunk that tied it for the ninth time, 72-72, with 46 seconds left and on Ben Finney's layup with 13 seconds left that put the Monarchs (11-5, 3-1) ahead. Julius Wells, who led the Dukes (7-7, 1-3) with 29 points, missed a 3-pointer with time running out. Wells scored 16 first-half points, including a dunk and a 3-pointer that forged ties after Old Dominion took a 20-12 lead, the game's largest. James Madison led 31-30 at the half after Keyon Carter's 3-pointer at the buzzer, but Old Dominion scored the first seven points of the second half to lead 37-31. Hassell and Gerald Lee scored 14 points each and Carter 13 for the Monarchs. Denzel Bowles scored 17 for the Dukes.
